div.p:
Bed and Board, or Cohabitation, belong to the Essence and Substance of Matrimony;
which made Erasmus and Bishop Hall say, That the distinction of those two from the
Bond, is merely Chimerical, and Fancy.

St. Ambrose says, a man may marry again, if he put away an adulterous Wife;
Theodoret said of a Wife who violated the Laws of Marriage: Therefore our Lord requires
the Bond or Tye of Marriage to be dissolved.
